A Grade I Area Court in Karu, Abuja, on Tuesday, ordered a 25-year-old man, Abah Mohammed, to clean the court premises for seven days, for stealing 10 bunches of plantain worth N15,000. The judge, Inuwa Maiwada, gave the order after Abah pleaded guilty to criminal trespass and theft. Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel, Ayotunde Adeyanju told the court that a housewife, Iyabo Onifade of Karu Market, Abuja reported the matter at the Karu Police Station on October 6. He said that the convict trespassed into her shop and stole 10 bunches of plantain, worth N15, 000. During police investigation, he said the stolen plantain was recovered from the convict. The prosecutor said the offence contravened the provisions of sections 348 and 288 of the Penal Code Law. The Nigerian Senate has told President Muhammadu Buhari to address Nigerians over the ongoing nationwide protests by the young people campaigning for an end to police brutality in the country. The upper chamber of the National Assembly made this call on Tuesday at its plenary session. READ ALSO: Tinubu Pleads With EndSARS Protesters To Back Down The Senate also urged the protesting youths to stop the protest to allow the Federal Government address their demands. Senate resolutions was sequel to a point of order motion on; “Matters of Urgent National Importance” brought by Senator Biodun Olujumi (PDP Ekiti).